Governor of Ekiti State, Ayodele Fayose has told a former Governor of the State and the All Progressive congress (APC) aspirant for July 14 governorship election in the state, John Kayode Fayemi not to rejoice yet, saying he will suffer the worse defeat of his political career in July 2018. Fayose stated this in a statement on Twitter.  He also thanked the APC  for giving Ekiti people, Kayode Fayemi who according to him was a candidate Ekiti people love to vote against and asked them to expect to suffer worse defeat compared to that of 201     Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook